article.headline: Wecker gets a double-double while Domenico scores 20
article.linkText: Wecker scores 25 as No. 4 K-State goes to 11-1
article.story:
DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- Kendra Wecker scored 25 points and grabbed
10 rebounds as No. 4 Kansas State beat Northern Illinois 63-58 Saturday.

	   Chelsea Domenico scored 20 points and Megan Mahoney added 13 for
Kansas State (11-1), which led 29-28 at the half.

	   Wecker was 11-for-20 from the floor and hit three of six shots from
beyond the arc for Kansas State, which shot 50 percent for the
game, compared to 34.4 percent for Northern Illinois.

	   The Huskies (4-6) managed to keep it close in the first half
with a balanced scoring attack and 3-for-4 shooting from 3-point
range. They finishing the game shooting 47.1 percent from
beyond the arc.

	   Four Huskies scored in double figures, led by Kim Boeding's 15
points. Stephanie Smith scored 14 points for Northern Illinois,
while Kristan Knake added 12.
